{
  "text": "The Solar obliquity is small relative to obliquities measured in many stars hosting extrasolar planets [CITATION_1] . These include examples of systems possessing the full range of misalignments, from aligned to antialigned [CITATION_2] . Could the stellar wind be responsible for these much more extreme misalignments? As a simple illustration, we plot in Figure 8 the probability of stellar obliquity exceeding a value \u03b2 (see Equation 26) for 0 = 10",
